data.name: XSAXEventKeeper
desc: This interface is used to manipulate element marks in a SAX event stream.

There are two kinds of element mark, one is element collector, which is used to collect a particular element from the SAX event stream; the other is blocker, which is used to block the SAX event stream.

methods.name: addBlocker
desc: Adds a new blocker on the next element in the SAX event stream.
No SAX event starting from the next element will be forwarded until this blocker is removed.

methods.name: addElementCollector
desc: Adds a new element collector on the next element in the SAX event stream.

methods.name: getCurrentBlockingNode
desc: Gets the element which current blocking happens.
This element is the working element of the first blocker in tree order.

methods.name: getElement
desc: Gets the element of an element mark.

methods.name: isBlocking
desc: Checks whether the SAX event stream is blocking.

methods.name: printBufferNodeTree
desc: Prints information about all buffered elements.

methods.name: setElement
desc: Sets the element of an element mark.
When an element is replaced outside of this interface, then uses this method can restore the link between an element mark and its working element.

methods.name: setNextHandler
desc: Sets the next document handler in the SAX chain.
This handler will receive SAX events forwarded by the SAXEventKeeper.
